Tanmay Shindolkar¶

Exploratory Data Analysis - Sports¶

  1. Problem Statement: Perform Exploratory Data Analysis on 'Indian Premiere League'

  2. As a sports analysts, find out the most successful teams, players and factors contributing win or loss of a team.

  3. Suggest teams or players a company should endorse for its products.

Dataset : matches.csv (https://bit.ly/34SRn3b)¶

team_wins_ser = df['winner'].value_counts()

    temp_df1 = pd.DataFrame({

In [27]:
#We will consider players who have played 10 or more seasons
no_of_balls = pd.DataFrame(df.groupby('batsman')['ball'].count()) #total number of matches played by each batsman
runs = pd.DataFrame(df.groupby('batsman')['batsman_runs'].sum()) #total runs of each batsman
seasons = pd.DataFrame(df.groupby('batsman')['season'].nunique()) #season = 1 implies played only 1 season

batsman_strike_rate = pd.DataFrame({'balls':no_of_balls['ball'],'run':runs['batsman_runs'],'season':seasons['season']})
batsman_strike_rate.reset_index(inplace = True)

batsman_strike_rate['strike_rate'] = batsman_strike_rate['run']/batsman_strike_rate['balls']*100
highest_strike_rate = batsman_strike_rate[batsman_strike_rate.season.isin([10,11])][['season','batsman','strike_rate']].sort_values(by = 'strike_rate',
                                                                                                      ascending = False)
plt.figure(figsize = (15,6))
sns.barplot(x='batsman', y='strike_rate', data = highest_strike_rate.head(10), hue = 'season', palette='Paired')
plt.title("Highest strike rates in IPL", fontsize = 20, fontweight = 'bold')
plt.xticks(rotation=50)
plt.xlabel("Player", size = 20)
plt.ylabel("Strike Rate", size = 20)
plt.show

# we will print numbers of fours hit by team
four_data=df[df['batsman_runs']==4]
four_data.groupby('batting_team')['batsman_runs'].agg([('runs by fours','sum'),('fours','count')])
# we will plot graph on four hit by players
batsman_four=four_data.groupby('batsman')['batsman_runs'].agg([('four','count')]).reset_index().sort_values('four',ascending=0)
ax=batsman_four.iloc[:10,:].plot('batsman','four',kind='bar',color='yellowgreen', figsize=(11,6))
plt.title("Numbers of fours hit by playes ", fontsize = 20, fontweight = 'bold')
plt.xticks(rotation=50)
plt.xlabel("Player name",fontsize=15)
plt.ylabel("No of fours",fontsize=15)
plt.show()

# we will print no of sixes hit by team

Conclusion :¶

The highest number of matches played in an IPL season was in 2011, 2012, and 2013.

The highest number of matches won by the Mumbai Indians, i.e., four matches out of 12 matches, Teams that bowl first have higher chances of winning than the team that bats first.

After winning the coin toss, more teams decide to field first.

In finals, teams that decide to field first win the matches more than the team that bats first.

In finals, most teams decide to field first after winning the toss.Sl Malinga, who has bowled the maximum number of extra balls, is followed by KA Pollard and DA Warner.

CH Gayle and AB de Villers are the top match-winners. It is interesting that out of the 12 IPL finals, nine times the team that won the toss was also the winner of the IPL.

Shikar Dhawan has the most four-hit games of any player.

CH Gayle has the most six-hit games of any player. The top three leading run scorers in the IPL are Virat Kohli, SK Raina, and RG Sharma.

The players with the highest number of matches played by their names are SK Raina and RG Sharma.

Top player of match ch Gayle
